  "prompt": "What is the origin of Kapoor caste?",
  "response": "The Kapoor surname is predominantly associated with the Punjabi Khatri community in India, particularly among Hindus and Sikhs. The Khatris are traditionally associated with trade and commerce, and the Kapoor name has become well known due to its association with the Indian film industry, particularly the Kapoor family of actors and filmmakers.\n\nThe origin of the Kapoor caste can be traced to the Khatri group, believed to have originated from the Punjab region. Historically, Khatris were known for their business acumen, and many transitioned into various professions over time, including those in the arts and entertainment sector.\n\nThe surname itself is thought to derive from the word \"Kapoor,\" which means \"camphor\" in Urdu and Hindi, suggesting a possible association with the trade of aromatic substances. The name gained prominence in the 20th century due to the contributions of the Kapoor family in Indian cinema, establishing the surname as a significant cultural identifier in Bollywood.\n\nIt's worth noting that discussions about caste and community can be complex, and the specifics can vary based on regional and social contexts.",
